ogy, finance, economy, medical sciences.). In this book,you will find lectures from two statisticians who are experts in this field.Gérard Grégoire, who has a long experience in econometrics and made a huge contribution to both this book and the session. He covers the basic elements of classical L2 time series, in the time domain as well as in the frequency domain, for univariate and multivariate series, and provides also tools for statistical inference. He gives an extensive presentation of ARMA and ARIMA series, and addresses some related advanced topics. He also devotes a chapter to linear Gaussian state space models and Kalman filtering that will be helpful to follow the last chapter written by Éric Moulines and collaborators: this final chapter is dedicated to state space models in a general framework and sequential MonteCarlo methods to leverage recursions generalizing the Kalman recursions for filtering and smoothing. Many practical exercises are given using the R environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aEarth Sciences. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Astrophysics.2bisacsh1 aDouc, Randal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrégoire, Gérard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGrégoire, Gérard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoulines, Éric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStoffer, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-2741-140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759827411423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782759827411/original  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aP